Reasoning: The paper deals with mathematical logic and set theory, which are typically classified under cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The use of realizability algebras suggests a connection to programming language theory, which falls under cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also involves examples and constructions, which could be classified under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The use of dependent choice and the construction of new models could be classified under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
